<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Suppose $A$ and $B$ are disjoint finite sets. ⦉

  ‖ Then $\num{A ∪ B} = \num{A} + \num{B}$ ⦉
</statement>

‖ This is often called the ❬addition principle❭ or the ❬rule of
  sum❭. ⦉
